metadata.name: contrapuntos #409
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodr√≠guez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: FluxMongers #50
metadata.description:
FluxMongers are very old beings from another dimension and their spin produces huge amounts of energy and this energy discharge is what causes the realities of MAGNETIK to be distorted or even to be torn apart. Their ethereal nature, speed and might make their movements almost to be perceived as some kind of choreography but this can only be called a dance of destruction. What you are looking at is a frame frozen in their deadly dance‚Ä¶

FluxMongers were inspired by light paintings where the painter uses one or few sources of light to draw in the air very quickly and the drawing is captured by long exposure.

After going live,

- press ‚Äò1‚Äô to get a hi-res version and ‚Äò2‚Äô to get a medium-res version (hopefully it will work :/)

- press 's' to save a png

metadata.name: Traffic #111
metadata.description:
Traffic is a companion piece to Scaffold. Whilst Scaffold was intended to capture a moment in time of a single mind, Traffic aims to represent a shared moment in a community.

Outputs can be beautiful, but can also be chaotic. They can be comprised of many contributions, but a single voice may drown out many others.

All royalties go to the original minter.

Keyboard commands:

s - save as png
h - toggle high resolution‚Ä®
b - toggle background texture
a - switch aspect ratio
r - new moment

metadata.name: The Space Inside #152
metadata.description:
Points fill in shapes on a warped noise field. The resulting images range from soft water colors to distorted, pixelated CRT screens. 

The image is drawn at 3000x3000px and scaled to the browser size. 

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save a screenshot. Image size is 3000x3000px
Press ‚Äôp‚Äô to pause/resume.

Features:
- Two palette sets
- Light or dark background
- 70% color image, 30% monochrome
- Various combinations of circles and rectangles
- All rectangles 
- 7 types of shapes: random circles, packed circles, checkerboard, orbs, ring, spiral, checkerboard and orbs
- Rectangles snap to a grid
- Fuzzy lines connected groups of drawing points
- Fuzzy lines around the dots
- Bright border on the shapes

Rare
- 9% to have a soft monochrome and color palette

metadata.name: The place where we were #147
metadata.description:
Emotions are responsible for the memory trace
Memories are mixed with imaginations and dreams.
Reality is a construct that requires memory.
What we feel is a part of reality that cannot be seen or shared
But those feelings were part of the place



S Save PNG Frame (in live mode)
G Save GIF Animation (in live mode)

Created with p5.js and gif.js by Victor Doval @vicdoval (2022)
Designed to be seen in Google Chrome 96.0.4664.45

metadata.name: Celebration in Times of Measure #63
metadata.description:
Intentionally developed by placing constraints on the process.

Everything is generated by code written in P5js.

Press '1' for the default, textured version
Press '2' to add outlines and see the form structure

Press '3' to see a flat, untextured version
Press '4' to add outlines (flat version)

Press 'e' to end/skip the initial animation
Press 'r' to restart/replay the animation
Press 's' to save current image (in live view)

Created by Walter Anderson (@noxiarb)
